fy persons, places, and events. English-Arabic and Arabic-English glossaries of terms further assist the reader.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aIslamic philosophyvEarly works to 1800. 0aPolitical sciencexPhilosophyvEarly works to 1800. 4aAncient History & Classical Studies. 4aPhilosophy. 4aPolitical Science & Political History.  aGreek philosophy, philosophy of Islam, Islamic political philosophy, Jewish philosophy, religion, Middle Eastern studies, translation.1 aButterworth, Charles E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311060674440uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150170032340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501700323423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501700323/original  a978-3-11-060674-4  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles